                Dual fuel stoves combine the best of both gas and electric stoves, offering a gas cooktop with an electric oven. While they provide versatility and precision, they also come with a unique set of repair needs. Issues can arise in both the gas and electric components, including problems with gas burners, electric heating elements, and electronic control systems. Repairing a dual fuel stove can be more involved and costly, with prices typically ranging from <b>$250 to $600</b>, depending on the nature of the problem. Regular maintenance should include checking both gas and electric components, cleaning burners, and ensuring that the control systems are functioning correctly. This holistic approach to maintenance can help prevent costly breakdowns and extend the life of the stove.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
