              <p>
                The cost of labor for commercial stove repair can vary widely depending on several factors, including the complexity of the issue, the type of stove, the region, and the specific service provider. Here are some general considerations to help you understand potential costs:
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <ol>
                <li><b>Hourly Rates: </b>Many repair services charge by the hour. In the United States, hourly rates for commercial appliance repair technicians typically range from $75 to $150 per hour. This can be higher in urban areas with a higher cost of living.</li>
                <li><b>Minimum Service Fee: </b>Some companies have a minimum service fee, which could cover the first hour of labor or a diagnostic fee. This fee usually ranges from $75 to $150.</li>
                <li><b>Complexity of the Repair: </b>Simpler repairs, like replacing a thermostat or igniter, might only take an hour or two. More complex issues, such as electrical problems or gas line issues, might take several hours to diagnose and fix, increasing labor costs.</li>
                <li><b>Emergency or After-Hours Service: </b>If you require emergency or after-hours service, expect to pay a premium. This could increase the hourly rate by 50% or more.</li>
                <li><b>Travel Fees: </b>Some technicians charge for travel time, especially if your location is outside their usual service area. This fee might be a flat rate or an additional hourly charge.</li>
                <li><b>Flat Rates: </b>Some companies offer flat-rate pricing for common repairs. This can provide more predictable costs, but it's essential to clarify what is included in the rate and if there are any potential additional charges.</li>
                <li><b>Maintenance Contracts: </b>For businesses that rely heavily on their stoves, signing a maintenance contract can sometimes be more cost-effective. These contracts often cover regular maintenance and minor repairs for a fixed annual fee.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <b>Example Cost Breakdown:</b>
