            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <b>Cleaning and Inspection </b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Burners and Grates: Regularly clean burners and grates to remove grease and food residues. This not only improves efficiency but also reduces the risk of fire hazards.</li>
                    <li>Ignition Systems: Inspect and clean ignition systems to ensure they are free from debris and functioning correctly. Faulty igniters are a common issue that can be avoided with regular cleaning.</li>
                    <li>Oven Interior: Clean the oven interior, including racks and walls, to prevent buildup that can affect cooking performance and food quality.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Checking Gas Lines and Connections </b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Gas Leaks: Inspect gas lines and connections for any signs of leaks. Use a gas leak detector or soapy water to check for bubbles at connection points.</li>
                    <li>Ventilation: Ensure that all ventilation systems are clear and functioning correctly to prevent the buildup of harmful gases.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Calibration and Adjustment </b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Thermostat Calibration: Regularly calibrate the thermostat to ensure accurate temperature control. Inconsistent temperatures can affect cooking times and food quality.</li>
                    <li>Burner Adjustment: Adjust burners to ensure an even flame and efficient gas usage. Uneven flames can indicate clogged or damaged burners that need attention.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Lubrication of Moving Parts </b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Hinges and Doors: Lubricate the hinges and doors to ensure smooth operation and prevent wear and tear.</li>
                    <li>Control Knobs: Ensure control knobs are functioning smoothly and are not loose or difficult to turn.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Professional Maintenance Service </b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Scheduled Inspections: Schedule professional maintenance services at least twice a year. Technicians can provide a thorough inspection, cleaning, and necessary repairs that might not be apparent during routine checks.</li>
                    <li>Service Records: Keep detailed records of all maintenance and repairs. This helps in tracking the health of your stove and identifying recurring issues.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Employee Training </b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Proper Usage: Train your staff on the proper use and cleaning of the stove. Correct usage reduces the likelihood of damage and extends the life of the appliance.</li>
                    <li>Daily Cleaning: Implement a daily cleaning routine to ensure that spills and residues are promptly cleaned, preventing buildup and potential damage.</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
